1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:02,562
This lecture covers the fundamentals of Docker

2
00:00:03,025 --> 00:00:05,450
a platform designed to help developers build

3
00:00:05,688 --> 00:00:06,338
deploy

4
00:00:06,562 --> 00:00:08,613
and run applications using containers

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,512
Containers allow a developer to package an application with all the necessary parts

6
00:00:13,725 --> 00:00:15,375
such as libraries and dependencies

7
00:00:15,762 --> 00:00:17,913
and ship it all out as one package

8
00:00:18,312 --> 00:00:18,950
With Docker

9
00:00:19,387 --> 00:00:23,725
you can ensure that the application will behave the same regardless of the environment it's running in

